---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Alert from '../../components/Alert.astro';
import Accordion from '../../components/Accordion.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Troubleshooting: Forgotten Admin Password Recovery"
	description="Lost access to router or filtering software. Learn how to recover or reset admin credentials safely."
>
	<Breadcrumb />

	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<header class="relative pb-6 border-b-[3px] border-blue-600 dark:border-blue-500 mb-8">
			<div class="inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mb-4 bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900 text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-100">Intermediate</div>
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 leading-tight">Forgotten Admin Password Recovery</h1>
			<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
				Lost access to router or filtering software. Recover or reset admin credentials safely.
			</p>
			<div class="flex gap-6 flex-wrap text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
				<span>‚è±Ô∏è Time Required: 10-30 minutes</span>
				<span>üîß Difficulty: Intermediate</span>
			</div>
		</header>

		<Alert type="warning">
			<strong>Important:</strong> Some password recovery methods will reset ALL settings, not just the password.
			Be prepared to reconfigure filtering from scratch.
		</Alert>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Router Admin Password Recovery</h2>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 mt-0">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">1</span>
					Try Default Credentials First
				</h3>
				<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If you never changed the password, it might still be the factory default:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Common Default Passwords:</h4>
				<ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2"><strong>Username:</strong> admin | <strong>Password:</strong> admin</li>
					<li class="mb-2"><strong>Username:</strong> admin | <strong>Password:</strong> password</li>
					<li class="mb-2"><strong>Username:</strong> admin | <strong>Password:</strong> (blank/empty)</li>
					<li class="mb-2"><strong>Username:</strong> administrator | <strong>Password:</strong> administrator</li>
				</ul>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Find Your Router's Defaults:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Check the label on the bottom/back of your router</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Look in the router's manual (or download from manufacturer website)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Visit <strong>RouterPasswords.com</strong> or <strong>DefaultPassword.com</strong></li>
					<li class="mb-2">Search Google for "[Your router model] default password"</li>
				</ol>

				<div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 my-4 rounded">
					<strong class="block text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mb-2">Popular Router Defaults:</strong>
					<ul class="ml-4 mb-0 text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100">
						<li class="mb-2"><strong>Netgear:</strong> admin / password</li>
						<li class="mb-2"><strong>TP-Link:</strong> admin / admin</li>
						<li class="mb-2"><strong>Linksys:</strong> admin / admin (or blank)</li>
						<li class="mb-2"><strong>ASUS:</strong> admin / admin</li>
						<li class="mb-2"><strong>D-Link:</strong> admin / (blank)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 mt-0">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">2</span>
					Check Common Password Storage Locations
				</h3>
				<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Before resetting, check if you saved the password somewhere:</p>
				<ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Browser password manager (check saved passwords)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Password manager app (1Password, LastPass, Bitwarden)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Sticky note on router or nearby</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Family shared password document</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Router setup documentation from ISP</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Email search for "router password" or "WiFi setup"</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 mt-0">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">3</span>
					Perform a Factory Reset
				</h3>
				<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If defaults don't work and password is truly lost, reset the router:</p>

				<Alert type="error">
					<strong>Warning:</strong> This erases ALL router settings:
					<ul>
						<li>WiFi network name and password</li>
						<li>DNS filtering settings</li>
						<li>Port forwarding rules</li>
						<li>Parental controls</li>
						<li>Guest network configuration</li>
					</ul>
					<p>You'll need to reconfigure everything from scratch. Write down current WiFi credentials first!</p>
				</Alert>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">How to Factory Reset Most Routers:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Locate the <strong>Reset button</strong> on the router (usually recessed, requires paperclip)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">While router is powered ON, press and hold Reset button</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Hold for <strong>10-30 seconds</strong> (LED lights will usually flash)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Release button when lights flash or after 30 seconds</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Wait 2-3 minutes for router to fully restart</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Router will now accept factory default credentials</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Brand-Specific Reset Instructions:</h4>

				<strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Netgear:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Press and hold Reset button for 7 seconds</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Power LED will blink amber</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Release when LED turns white</li>
				</ol>

				<strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">TP-Link:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Hold Reset button for 10 seconds while powered on</li>
					<li class="mb-2">All LEDs will turn off and back on</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Release button</li>
				</ol>

				<strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">ASUS:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Hold Reset button for 5-10 seconds</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Power LED will flash slowly</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Release when LED stops flashing</li>
				</ol>

				<strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Linksys:</strong>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Hold Reset button for 10 seconds</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Power light will flash</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Release and wait for restart</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
				<h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 mt-0">
					<span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl">4</span>
					Reconfigure After Reset
				</h3>
				<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Once reset, you must set everything up again:</p>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Immediate Steps:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Connect to router using Ethernet cable or default WiFi</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Access router admin (usually 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.0.1)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Log in with factory default credentials</li>
					<li class="mb-2"><strong>IMMEDIATELY change admin password</strong> (and write it down!)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Change WiFi network name and password</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Restore Filtering:</h4>
				<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li class="mb-2">Configure DNS filtering (see our <a href="/guides/dns-filtering" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-700 dark:hover:text-blue-300">DNS filtering guide</a>)</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Re-enable parental controls</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Set up guest network if needed</li>
					<li class="mb-2">Configure any other security settings</li>
				</ol>

				<Alert type="info">
					<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Take screenshots of all important router settings so you have a backup if this happens again.
				</Alert>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Filtering Software Password Recovery</h2>

			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mt-6">
				<Accordion title="OpenDNS Account" defaultOpen={true}>
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Forgot Password:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Go to <strong>dashboard.opendns.com</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Forgot Password?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter your email address</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Check email for password reset link</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Create new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Forgot Email:</h4>
					<ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Check browser auto-fill when visiting dashboard</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Search email for "OpenDNS" to find account confirmation</li>
						<li class="mb-2">If truly lost, create a new account and reconfigure DNS settings</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="CleanBrowsing Account">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Free Service:</h4>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">No account required for free DNS filtering. Just use the DNS servers.</p>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Paid Service:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Go to <strong>cleanbrowsing.org/login</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Forgot your password?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter registered email</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Follow email instructions to reset</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Qustodio">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Parent Account Recovery:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Visit <strong>family.qustodio.com</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter your email address</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Check email for reset link (check spam folder)</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Set new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Cannot Remove from Device:</h4>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If you can't log into Qustodio to uninstall it:</p>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Contact Qustodio support with proof of device ownership</li>
						<li class="mb-2">They can reset your account or provide removal instructions</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Last resort: Factory reset device (nuclear option)</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Net Nanny">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Account Recovery:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Go to <strong>admin.netnanny.com</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Forgot Password"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter email and follow instructions</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Lost Access Completely:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Contact Net Nanny support: 1-800-485-3011</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Provide proof of purchase</li>
						<li class="mb-2">They can reset your account</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Bark">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Parent App Password Reset:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Open Bark parent app</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Tap <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong> on login screen</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter email address</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Check email for code</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter code and set new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Cannot Access Email:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Contact Bark support via website</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Verify identity with billing information</li>
						<li class="mb-2">They can update email or reset account</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Circle by Disney">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">App Password Reset:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Open Circle app</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Login screen ‚Üí <strong>"Forgot Password?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter email and follow instructions</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Physical Device Reset:</h4>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If you have the physical Circle device:</p>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Press and hold button on Circle device for 10 seconds</li>
						<li class="mb-2">LED will flash red</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Device resets to factory settings</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Reconfigure in app</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Device-Level Controls Password Recovery</h2>

			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mt-6">
				<Accordion title="iOS Screen Time Passcode">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Forgot Screen Time Passcode:</h4>

					<strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">iOS 13.4 or Later:</strong>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Settings ‚Üí Screen Time</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Tap <strong>"Change Screen Time Passcode"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Tap again to confirm</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Select <strong>"Forgot Passcode?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter Apple ID and password used to set up Screen Time</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Create new Screen Time passcode</li>
					</ol>

					<strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Older iOS Versions:</strong>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">No recovery option available. Must factory reset device:</p>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Back up device to iCloud or computer first</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Settings ‚Üí General ‚Üí Transfer or Reset iPhone</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Erase All Content and Settings</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Set up as new device or restore backup</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Screen Time restrictions will be removed</li>
					</ol>

					<Alert type="warning">
						Factory reset is drastic. Try Apple Support first‚Äîthey may be able to help verify identity and reset.
					</Alert>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Android Family Link">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Parent Account Password:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Visit <strong>accounts.google.com</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Follow Google account recovery process</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Verify identity with phone number or recovery email</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Cannot Remove Family Link:</h4>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If parent account is lost and child device is locked:</p>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Factory reset is the only option</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Power off device</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Boot into recovery mode (varies by device, usually Volume Down + Power)</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Select "Wipe data/factory reset"</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Device will be completely wiped</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Windows Family Safety">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Microsoft Account Recovery:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Go to <strong>account.microsoft.com</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Sign in"</strong> then <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter email/phone/Skype name</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Verify identity (security code to email/phone)</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Create new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Child Account Locked:</h4>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">If you can't remove Family Safety from child's Windows account:</p>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Boot into Safe Mode (restart, hold Shift, Troubleshoot ‚Üí Advanced ‚Üí Startup Settings ‚Üí Safe Mode)</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Log in as local administrator</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Remove child from family via Settings ‚Üí Accounts ‚Üí Family</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Or create new local admin account and migrate data</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="macOS Screen Time">
					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Recovery Process:</h4>
					<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Similar to iOS, but slightly different:</p>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">System Settings (or Preferences) ‚Üí Screen Time</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Click lock icon, try to change passcode</li>
						<li class="mb-2"><strong>"Forgot Passcode?"</strong></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Enter Apple ID credentials</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Reset passcode</li>
					</ol>

					<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">If Apple ID Method Fails:</h4>
					<ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						<li class="mb-2">Boot into Recovery Mode (restart, hold Cmd+R)</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Utilities ‚Üí Terminal</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Type: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono">resetpassword</code></li>
						<li class="mb-2">Select user account</li>
						<li class="mb-2">Option to reset Screen Time passcode appears</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-10">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Prevention: Never Lose Passwords Again</h2>

			<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-4">Use a Password Manager</h3>
			<p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Store all filtering/router passwords securely:</p>
			<ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
				<li class="mb-2"><strong>1Password:</strong> $2.99/month, excellent family sharing</li>
				<li class="mb-2"><strong>Bitwarden:</strong> Free (premium $10/year), open source</li>
				<li class="mb-2"><strong>LastPass:</strong> Free for single device, premium for families</li>
				<li class="mb-2"><strong>Apple Keychain:</strong> Free, built into Apple devices</li>
				<li class="mb-2"><strong>Google Password Manager:</strong> Free, built into Chrome</li>
